com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core
Interface AttributeMetaData

public interface AttributeMetaData

A representation of the model object 'Attribute Meta Data'. Properties that can be applied to any attribute in a DeployModelObject (including ExtendedAttributes).

The following features are supported:

  • Attribute Name
  • Description
  • Encrypted
  • Encryption Required
  • Mutable
  • Optional
  • Parameter

See Also:
CorePackage.getAttributeMetaData()

isParameter

boolean isParameter()
Returns the value of the 'Parameter' attribute. The default value is "false". Template validation MUST NOT complain about the value of any (extended) attribute tagged as a parameter (but Publish validation MUST complain if publishing would fail with the attribute at it's current value. 'Deploy' validation MAY complain.) 'Parameter' is a hint to validators indicating that an attribute's value isn't finalized. It's a hint to to 'topology factories' of good customization points on topology templates.

Returns:
the value of the 'Parameter' attribute.
See Also:
isSetParameter(), unsetParameter(), setParameter(boolean), CorePackage.getAttributeMetaData_Parameter()
